The Security Council (SC) is the most powerful organ of the United Nations (UN). It comprises 15 members, five of which are permanent and 10 of which are elected for a two-year term. The permanent members (China, France, the Russian Federation, the United Kingdom, and the United States) are veto-wielding members. The SC is responsible for the maintenance of international peace and security. The SC is also authorized to take measures against threats to international peace and security; it may, for example, impose economic or diplomatic sanctions.
The General Assembly (GA) is the principal deliberative, policymaking, and representative organ of the UN.

when was the Star Spangled Banner written? Answers 1 Francis Scott Key was a lawyer and an amateur poet. In 1814, during the War of 1812, he was aboard a British ship trying to negotiate the release of an American prisoner. The British ship fired on Fort McHenry in Baltimore. Key watched all night, and in the morning, he saw the American flag still waving. He later wrote a poem about the experience, and called it "The Defense of Fort McHenry." Key's poem was set to music, and in 1931, it became our national anthem.
